Title: The "what's an agent" discourse is so funny to me. Imagine people in 1960 being like: What's a compu...
Author: Jake Koenig
Summary: The "what's an agent" discourse is so funny to me. Imagine people in 1960 being like: What's a computer program? Some people mean punch cards. Others cobol. Some talk about abstract "Turing machines". Clearly the term has no meaning or value
